From: Trung Lê <8@tle.id.au>
Subject: include: add config.h stub forwarding to cde_config.h

Fedora's motif-devel ships private (P-suffix) headers — e.g.
Xm/DisplayP.h — that begin with:

  #ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
  #include <config.h>
  #endif

CDE compiles with -DHAVE_CONFIG_H (it owns include/cde_config.h via
AC_CONFIG_HEADERS), so when DtWidget pulls in Xm/DisplayP.h the Motif
header tries to include a config.h that doesn't exist on the search
path, breaking the build:

  /usr/include/Xm/DisplayP.h:27:10: fatal error: config.h: No such
  file or directory

Provide a tiny stub at include/config.h that forwards to cde_config.h.
The directory is already on the include search path via -I../../include
in the per-Makefile flags, so Motif's lookup resolves to this stub
without changing CDE's own include strategy.
---
 include/config.h | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 include/config.h

diff --git a/include/config.h b/include/config.h
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/include/config.h
@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@
+/*
+ * Stub so Motif's private (P-suffix) headers can resolve <config.h>.
+ * CDE itself uses cde_config.h (see AC_CONFIG_HEADERS in configure.ac);
+ * this file just forwards the include for the benefit of motif-devel.
+ */
+#include "cde_config.h"
